comment: Axiom of Replacement (similar to Axiom Rep of [BellMachover] p. 463). The antecedent tells us ` ph ` is analogous to a "function" from ` x ` to ` y ` (although it is not really a function since it is a wff and not a class). In the consequent we postulate the existence of a set ` z ` that corresponds to the "image" of ` ph ` restricted to some other set ` w ` . The hypothesis says ` z ` must not be free in ` ph ` . (Contributed by NM, 26-Nov-1995.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 14-Oct-2016.)
